- **?probe-enumeration-misconfigured**: `+` (was new) — sub-200ms burst across all 5 sanctioned sentinels in a single tick is fully consistent with "full sentinel list fired in one invocation." Cron active and zero non-5710 alerts support an operational monitoring host. Cannot upgrade: observationally indistinguishable from `?monitoring-bait-triggered`; process-list inconclusive (short-lived script already exited); no workload-ownership anchor available. Prior-hour per-event timing not reported — needed to determine if this burst pattern recurs (which would flip toward misconfiguration) or is isolated (bait).

- **?monitoring-bait-triggered**: `+` (was new) — single discrete sub-200ms burst consistent with a one-off manual trigger; only sanctioned sentinel usernames; zero successful auth; no `monitoring_bait` process found (inconclusive — short-lived scripts exit, absence cannot refute). Cannot upgrade: no ownership evidence confirming manual trigger; process absence is formally uninformative.

- **?monitoring-host-compromise**: `-` (was new) — all predicted indicators absent: zero non-sentinel usernames across 4h, zero 5501/5715 from 172.22.0.10 in the 4h+5min window, zero non-5710 alerts on monitoring-host, cron active, no anomalous processes. Strongly disfavored but bounded by two explicit epistemic limits from HYPOTHESIZE: (a) *adversary may stay within sentinel set deliberately*, (b) FIM coverage on monitoring-host unverified (alert absence ≠ event absence). No pre-registered refutation shape met.

- **?internal-credential-guessing**: `--` (was new) — sub-200ms automated burst of 5 events with 5 distinct sentinel usernames directly contradicts both core predictions (manual implies low volume; "real-looking usernames"). HYPOTHESIZE flagged "preliminary refutation already holds" from SCREEN; GATHER makes it unambiguous. No formal `r{N}` ID — see self-report.

- **?compromise-followup**: `--` (was new) — zero rule-5501/5715 events from 172.22.0.10 across the comprehensive 4h+5min window (far exceeding the 60s checked in SCREEN). HYPOTHESIZE explicitly defined the refutation shape: *"Absence over the full burst window + 5 min forward = `?compromise-followup` cleared."* Named narrative refutation: absence-of-success-in-forward-window. No formal `r{N}` ID — see self-report.

